{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place ginger and sugar in mixing bowl then grind <nobr>5 sec\/speed 8<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl then grind again <nobr>5 sec\/speed 8<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl.","Add mango then purée <nobr>10 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr>.","Add yoghurt, coconut milk and vanilla extract then mix <nobr>10 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>. Transfer mixture to shallow freezer proof containers then freeze overnight or for at least 10 hours.","To serve, remove from freezer, tip out and cut into squares (3 cm x 3 cm). Place ⅓ squares in mixing bowl and churn <nobr>10 sec\/speed 8<\/nobr> then tip out into a serving bowl and set aside. Place another ⅓ squares in mixing bowl and churn <nobr>10 sec\/speed 8<\/nobr> then tip out into serving bowl and set aside. Place remaining squares in mixing bowl and churn <nobr>10 sec\/speed 8<\/nobr> then tip out into serving bowl. Serve immediately garnished with mango slices and fresh mint leaves."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["25 g fresh root ginger, cut in round slices (2 mm)","200 g sugar","650 g mango, ripe, cut in pieces, plus extra for serving","900 g plain yoghurt","380 g coconut milk, unsweetened","1 tsp natural vanilla extract","1 sprig fresh mint leaves, for garnish"]}],"id":"r95520","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-zSpEEOi7wys\/XZaorlRLt7I\/AAAAAAAAhMg\/w9WnWHcT6HMCS2Iv2uIYr0TUyH8P3Y7eACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_v61n4wQSlBJZ6Xpz.png","title":"Mango and Ginger Frozen Yoghurt","publishedAt":"2015-09-01T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"6.3 g","fat":"13 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"46.6 g","calories":"1373 kJ \/ 328 kcal"},"usefulItems":"freezer proof containers, serving bowl, long sharp knife, freezer","hintsAndTricks":["Freeze the ice cream mixture in ice cube trays rather than cutting into squares if preferred."],"basicInfo":["easy","5m","12h 5m","8 portions"]}